Layouts can range from a simple visual filter to adjust the opacity of the background video to an animated flowchart overlay which can be filled with additional text. This article takes a closer look at both kinds of layout elements, and provides a reference on how to configure them.

## Add info layouts
To add an info overlay to the selected scene or pop-up:

- Open the **scene editor**.

- In the **sidebar**, go to **Layouts **&gt; **Info**.

- Select one of the overlays and click **Add**.

The selected info layout will be added to the timeline.

> Note

Info overlays fill the entire video screen and canâ€™t be resized.

### Configure info layouts
Click on the timeline layer of the layout element to open the settings.

The number of available configuration options depends on the selected layout, for example, it can contain multiple text and image elements which can be formatted individually. The following configuration options are common to all layout elements:

- **Duration: **Enter the exact timestamps to control the start and end of the element

![Layout settings interface displaying main text, notes, and images for a project.](data:image/png;base64,)Example of an info layout element containing text and images

## Add filters
To add a filter to the selected scene or pop-up:

- Open the **scene editor**.

- In the **sidebar**, go to **Layouts **&gt; **Filters**.

- Select one of the filters and click **Add**.

The selected filter will be added to the timeline.

> Note

Filters fill the entire video screen and canâ€™t be resized.

### Configure filter elements
Click on the filter element in the playback area or its timeline layer to open the settings:

- **Duration: **Enter the exact timestamps to control the start and end of the element

![Layout settings display duration, start, end times, and delete option for adjustments.](data:image/png;base64,)

## Upload your own files
To use your own layout files, they must be uploaded to the file drive:

- Open the **scene editor**.

- In the **sidebar**, open the **Layouts **palette.

- Click **My files** &gt; **Upload** and select a file from your local storage.

> Info

Only one file can be uploaded at a time. The supported layout formats are:

**JSON**

- Add the uploaded file to the scene or pop-up.

### FAQ
#### Whatâ€™s the difference between a filter and an info layout?
Infos and filters are different types of layout elements. Filters typically add a visual animation or image correction, while info layouts can contain both animated visual elements, as well as text or images which are displayed in the animation.
